               <head>Three Sufi works</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Collection of three Sufi works. Not dated; early nineteenth century. Detached binding, with spine missing; printed decorative paper on exterior; descriptive labels; boards wormeaten; text block bound. Microfilm: IOL Neg 2267. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_962-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="16r">ff. 1v-16r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Sufi treatise by an unnamed author consisting of general points of guidence for novices in florid and poetic prose. </p>
                        <p>Transcribed in nastaʿlīq tending to shikastah āmīz. </p>
                        <p>Not dated. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21801">Ādāb al-murīdīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21801">آداب المريدين</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104964" n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_962-item2">
                     <locus from="17v" to="35r">ff. 17v-35r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7463">Nūr Allāh "Mīr Shīrvānī"</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7463">نور الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21800">Aqvāl-i buzurgān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21800">اقوال بزرگان</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Brief treatise expounding the Sufi doctrines of generosity and brotherhood, with many quotes from early masters, followed in the latter half by the author's remarks addressed to his friends beginning <q>ay ʿazīz</q>. See BL MS Or 2063 for a work of similar content. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_962-item3">
                     <locus from="35v" to="36r">ff. 35v-36r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Fragment from a Sufi treatise by an unnamed author consisting of general points of guidence for novices in florid and poetic prose. See item a. </p>
                        <p>Not dated. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21801">Ādāb al-murīdīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21801">آداب المريدين</title>
                  </msItem>
